The paper presents an approach to event coreference resolution using a neural network architecture with novel regularization terms. This approach involves supervised representation learning and clustering, which are common techniques in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new general approach to solving coreference and clustering problems with representation learning, which could also fit into sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach on a corpus, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
